        ]
      },
      "text": [
        "هِ تَعَالَى مَنْ ذَا الَّذِي يُقْرِضُ اللَّهَ قَرْضاً حَسَناً فَيُضاعِفَهُ لَهُ وَ لَهُ أَجْرٌ كَرِيمٌ قَالَ صِلَةُ الْإِمَامِ فِي دَوْلَةِ الْفَسَقَةِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "<a id=\"_Toc492473591\">H 14909</a> – Muhammad Bin Ahmad, from Abdullah Bin Al-Salt, from Yunus, and from Abdul Aziz Bin Al-Muhtady, from a man, who has narrated the following:",
          "<span class=\"first-chapter-phrase\"><span class=\"first-in-chapter character-a\">A</span>bu Al-Hassan the Last</span><sup>asws</sup> regarding the Statement of the High: <span class=\"ibTxt\">“<a href=\"/#/books/quran:57#h11\"><a href=\"/books/quran:57#h11\">[57:11]</a></a> Who is he that will Loan to Allah a beautiful loan? for (Allah) will increase it manifold to his credit, and he will have (besides) a liberal Reward”</span>, he<sup>asws</sup> said; ‘It is the ‘good’ towards the Imam<sup>asws</sup> during the government of the mischief’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "462. Yunus, from Sinan Bin Tareyf who said: I heard Abu Abdullah (a.s.) saying: ‘It is befitting for ‘لِلْمُؤْمِنِ’ the Believer that he should fear Allah (azwj) with such a fear as if he is overlooking upon the Fire, and hope with such a hope as if he is from the inhabitants of the Paradise’. Then said: ‘Allah (azwj) is with the expectation of His (azwj) servant. If he expects good, so it will be good, and if he expects evil, so it will be evil’."
        ]
      }
    },
